# gald3r Project Rules — Void Editor
# Void is an open-source VS Code fork that reads .cursorrules for AI project guidance.
# Docs: https://voideditor.com

## Project Context

This project uses the gald3r framework for AI-assisted development.

## Task Management

- Tasks tracked in `.gald3r/TASKS.md` and `.gald3r/tasks/`
- Status: [📋] pending | [🔄] in-progress | [🔍] awaiting review | [✅] complete
- Reference active tasks before making changes

## Code Conventions

- Commit format: `type(scope): description` (feat, fix, chore, docs, refactor, test)
- No AI co-author footers in commits (C-021)
- All documentation goes in `docs/` — not project root

## Architecture

- Read `.gald3r/SUBSYSTEMS.md` before modifying core systems
- Check `.gald3r/CONSTRAINTS.md` for active project constraints
- Bug discovery: log pre-existing bugs in `.gald3r/BUGS.md`, fix current-task bugs inline

## Privacy Note

Void sends prompts directly to your model provider — no proprietary backend.
Configure your provider in `.vscode/settings.json`.
